This paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category as it deals with the subtyping relation in Java and other generic nominally-typed OO programming languages. It may also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category as it explores the use of operads, which are a mathematical structure used in category theory. Additionally, it could be classified under Software Engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with understanding the type systems of programming languages. The paper also touches on Type Theory (cs.TY) and Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) due to its focus on the subtyping relation and the use of operads to model self-similar phenomena.
